
                                            Preston Titus was stabbed to death at his home a military base about two weeks ago.
                                         CAPE TOWN - A second suspect has been arrested in connection with the murder of a soldier in Oudtshoorn. The man was tracked down in Port Elizabeth. Preston Titus was stabbed to death at his home located on a military base about two weeks ago. A 23-year-old suspect was arrested shortly after the murder. The police's Malcolm Pojie said: “A thorough investigation by the investigating team led the members to arrest a 30-year-old man in connection with the murder of the SANDF member Preston Titus. The man was charged and appeared in the Oudtshoorn Magistrates Court. Unfortunately, the outcome is not known yet.” (Edited by Shimoney Regter)